WEBVTT

00:00.601 --> 00:02.968
<i> PREVIOUSLY ON "NASHVILLE"...</i>

00:02.969 --> 00:05.336
YOU GUYS ARE REALLY GOOD
TOGETHER. SHOULD I BE WORRIED?
NO. JUST MUSIC.

00:05.339 --> 00:06.705
THE TRUTH IS, I'M GAY.

00:06.707 --> 00:08.673
[ REPORTERS MURMURING ]

00:08.675 --> 00:11.175
I DON'T THINK GOING OUT ON TOUR
RIGHT NOW IS A GOOD IDEA.

00:11.177 --> 00:12.443
I'VE GOT
A FINISHED ALBUM,

00:12.444 --> 00:13.710
AND THEY'RE TRYING
TO KEEP ME OFF THE ROAD.

00:13.712 --> 00:15.578
I JUST SIGNED HER
TO MY LABEL!

00:15.580 --> 00:17.580
I NEEDED THIS.

00:17.582 --> 00:19.181
MORE THAN YOU NEED US?

00:19.183 --> 00:20.883
YOU'RE GOING TO PRISON,
TEDDY.

00:20.884 --> 00:22.584
AT LEAST LET ME TALK
TO MY DAUGHTERS.

00:22.586 --> 00:23.751
HE NEEDS
A LIVER TRANSPLANT.

00:23.753 --> 00:25.419
Caleb: YOUR SISTER
REALLY IS A LIFESAVER.

00:25.421 --> 00:26.520
[ PADDLES WHINE, THUMP ]
STILL NOTHING.

00:26.522 --> 00:27.521
I HAVE SOME BAD NEWS.

00:30.259 --> 00:32.559
A.J. Hammer: WE ARE HERE TONIGHT
LIVE IN THE HEART OF HOLLYWOOD

00:32.561 --> 00:35.028
AT THE RED-CARPET PREMIERE
OF "SHENANDOAH GIRL."

00:35.030 --> 00:37.230
THIS MOVIE MARKS
THE FEATURE-FILM DEBUT

00:37.232 --> 00:39.632
OF COUNTRY-MUSIC SWEETHEART
JULIETTE BARNES.

00:39.634 --> 00:43.669
Female reporter:
IT'S HARD TO IMAGINE ANYONE
HOTTER THAN JULIETTE BARNES

00:43.671 --> 00:46.038
ANYWHERE IN ENTERTAINMENT
TONIGHT.

00:46.040 --> 00:48.507
WITH JULIETTE BARNES'
MUCH-ANTICIPATED ALBUM

00:48.509 --> 00:50.408
DUE OUT
IN JUST ABOUT A WEEK,

00:50.410 --> 00:53.177
COUNTRY MUSIC IS GOING TO
HAVE TO TAKE A BACKSEAT

00:53.179 --> 00:54.478
TO HOLLYWOOD TONIGHT.

00:54.480 --> 00:57.113
[ CROWD SHOUTING,
CAMERAS CLICKING ]

01:37.120 --> 01:38.752
JULIETTE JUST PULLED UP.
SOUNDS GOOD.

01:38.754 --> 01:40.153
WAS THAT JEFF?

01:40.155 --> 01:41.304
JUST CHECKING IN
FROM NEW YORK

01:41.305 --> 01:42.454
TO MAKE SURE
EVERYTHING'S GOING SMOOTHLY.

01:42.457 --> 01:44.723
I TOLD HIM YOU WERE PERFECT,
AS ALWAYS.

01:44.725 --> 01:46.357
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

01:46.359 --> 01:47.558
SERIOUSLY?

01:47.560 --> 01:49.326
JEFF'S NOT EVEN HERE,

01:49.328 --> 01:51.494
AND LAYLA'S TAKING UP TIME
ON<i> MY</i> RED CARPET.

01:51.496 --> 01:53.796
HE'S BUSY MAKING SURE
YOU'RE THE NEW FACE OF CHANEL.

01:53.798 --> 01:56.098
THAT'S NOT THE POINT
I WAS MAKING.

01:56.100 --> 01:57.866
YOU AND I BOTH KNOW
THAT HAVING LAYLA HERE

01:57.868 --> 02:00.168
JUST MAKES YOU SEEM LIKE
A BIGGER STAR BY COMPARISON.

02:00.170 --> 02:01.235
GIVE ME A BREAK.

02:01.237 --> 02:02.669
JEFF BROUGHT YOU ON
TO MY TEAM

02:02.671 --> 02:04.237
TO FILL IN FOR HIM
WHEN HE'S GONE,

02:04.239 --> 02:05.688
NOT TO STROKE MY EGO.

02:05.689 --> 02:07.138
AND HE BROUGHT YOU ON
TO<i> HER</i> TEAM

02:07.141 --> 02:08.573
BECAUSE HE'S SLEEPING
WITH HER, RIGHT?

02:08.575 --> 02:11.676
[ CAMERAS CLICKING ]

02:11.678 --> 02:12.877
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

02:12.879 --> 02:14.511
UNBELIEVABLE.

02:14.513 --> 02:16.346
WHATEVER.
THEY DESERVE EACH OTHER.

02:16.348 --> 02:18.247
A.J.: JULIETTE.

02:18.249 --> 02:19.248
HI!

02:19.250 --> 02:21.116
YOU LOOK LOVELY.
THANK YOU!

02:21.118 --> 02:23.218
WELL, YOU MUST BE
SUPER-EXCITED --

02:23.220 --> 02:25.119
YOUR FIRST
HOLLYWOOD PREMIERE.

02:25.121 --> 02:26.620
I AM.
IT'S A DREAM COME TRUE.

02:26.622 --> 02:29.489
AND THE REVIEWS, BY THE WAY,
HAVE BEEN SIMPLY FANTASTIC.

02:29.491 --> 02:30.756
WE'RE ACTUALLY STARTING
TO HEAR SOME OSCAR BUZZ.

02:30.758 --> 02:32.224
OH, MY GOSH. WOW.

02:32.226 --> 02:34.759
I -- I'M JUST SO EXCITED
TO BE HERE

02:34.761 --> 02:37.795
AND CELEBRATE EVERYBODY WHO
HELPED MAKE THIS WONDERFUL FILM.

02:37.797 --> 02:40.297
I JUST WISH NOAH WEST
COULD BE HERE WITH US.

02:40.299 --> 02:41.865
OH, THAT GUY'S OFF MAKING
ANOTHER MOVIE ELSEWHERE...

02:41.867 --> 02:44.084
HI. [ CHUCKLES ]
...BUT<i> I'M</i> HERE.

02:44.085 --> 02:46.302
ALL RIGHT, NOW WE'RE JOINED BY
THE ONE AND ONLY LUKE WHEELER.

02:46.304 --> 02:47.369
IT'S NICE TO SEE YOU,
LUKE.

02:47.371 --> 02:48.587
GOOD TO SEE YOU,
A.J.

02:48.588 --> 02:49.804
AND YOU GUYS ARE
PLAYING THE STAPLES CENTER

02:49.806 --> 02:51.572
AS PART OF YOUR TOUR
TOMORROW.

02:51.574 --> 02:53.740
I GOT TO BELIEVE YOU'RE HAVING
SOME BIG FUN OUT THERE.

02:53.742 --> 02:55.408
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
WE'RE HAVING A GREAT TIME.

02:55.410 --> 02:58.277
I-I'M SO LUCKY TO HAVE JULIETTE
OUT ON THE ROAD WITH ME.

02:58.279 --> 03:00.712
AND, HELL, SHE'S NOT ONLY
A BIG-TIME MOVIE STAR,

03:00.714 --> 03:02.280
BUT SHE'S GOT AN ALBUM
COMING OUT.

03:02.282 --> 03:03.814
IT'S GONNA MAKE HER
COUNTRY'S #1 ARTIST AGAIN.

03:03.816 --> 03:04.915
JUST YOU WATCH.

03:04.917 --> 03:07.034
ON<i> MY</i> LABEL,
BY THE WAY.

03:07.035 --> 03:09.152
THAT'S RIGHT -- JULIETTE,
YOU LEFT THE GREAT RAYNA JAMES

03:09.154 --> 03:10.820
FOR WHEELIN' DEALIN'
RECORDS.

03:10.822 --> 03:11.921
HAVING
ANY SECOND THOUGHTS?

03:11.923 --> 03:13.356
[ LAUGHS ]
NOPE.

03:13.357 --> 03:14.790
IT'S THE BEST DECISION
I'VE EVER MADE.

03:14.792 --> 03:16.691
Woman:
JULIETTE! I LOVE YOU!

03:16.693 --> 03:18.659
Rayna: YOU KNOW WHAT?
I DON'T EVEN WANT TO RESPOND.

03:18.661 --> 03:21.561
WE'VE BEEN MIRED IN LEGAL CRAP
WITH THIS GIRL FOR A MONTH.

03:21.563 --> 03:23.329
I'M DONE.

03:23.331 --> 03:25.197
LUKE CAN HAVE HER.

03:25.199 --> 03:27.566
OKAY, BUT THE PRESS
IS HAVING A FIELD DAY.

03:27.568 --> 03:30.468
"JULIETTE BARNES DISSES
RAYNA JAMES ON THE RED CARPET."

03:30.470 --> 03:32.169
I DON'T CARE. I'M NOT GONNA
MAKE THIS INTO A CATFIGHT.

03:32.171 --> 03:33.904
GIRLS!
COME ON DOWN, PLEASE!

03:33.906 --> 03:35.538
I KNOW. I JUST WANTED IT
ON YOUR RADAR.

03:35.540 --> 03:36.872
AND THERE'S A LOT
OF CHATTER OUT THERE

03:36.874 --> 03:38.340
ABOUT HOW YOU HAVEN'T
SAID ANYTHING

03:38.342 --> 03:39.708
BEYOND CONFIRMING
SHE LEFT THE LABEL.

03:39.710 --> 03:41.609
I'LL BE REALLY HONEST
WITH YOU.

03:41.611 --> 03:44.211
I'VE HAD TO DO
A LOT OF LETTING GO LATELY.

03:44.213 --> 03:45.779
THIS ONE --
GONNA BE REAL EASY.

03:45.781 --> 03:48.548
I KNOW. I'M SORRY.

03:48.550 --> 03:50.416
HEY, UM, SWEETHEART,
DO YOU HAVE YOUR SOCCER BAG?

03:50.418 --> 03:52.051
YEP.
OKAY.

03:52.052 --> 03:53.685
LISTEN TO ME.
I AM DONE WITH JULIETTE.

03:53.687 --> 03:55.186
I JUST WANT IT
TO BE OFFICIAL.

03:55.188 --> 03:56.620
LET'S JUST SIGN THE PAPERS,
PLEASE.

03:56.622 --> 03:58.788
OKAY, WELL, LUKE'S LAWYERS
ARE SENDING OVER

03:58.790 --> 04:00.456
THE FINAL PAPERWORK
FOR HER BUYOUT TODAY.

04:00.458 --> 04:02.191
Thank you. Bye.

04:02.193 --> 04:03.693
[ SIGHS ]

04:03.694 --> 04:05.194
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S GO SEE AUNT BEVERLY.

04:08.832 --> 04:09.831
[ MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY ]

04:09.833 --> 04:11.599
DO YOU THINK
SHE KNOWS WE'RE HERE?

04:11.601 --> 04:13.518
<i> YOU</i> DIDN'T.
RIGHT, MOM?

04:13.519 --> 04:15.436
WELL, YOU KNOW,
WHAT I HAD WAS DIFFERENT.

04:15.438 --> 04:17.838
SHE HAD AN ANEURYSM.
I HAD AN INDUCED COMA.

04:17.840 --> 04:19.339
BUT I HOPE SHE DOES.

04:19.341 --> 04:20.373
YEAH.

04:20.375 --> 04:21.974
DOCTOR'S SAYING --

04:21.976 --> 04:24.710
SHE'S DOING GOOD.

04:24.712 --> 04:27.345
WHOLE BUNCH OF ACTIVITY
ON HER E.E.G. SCAN THIS MORNING.

04:27.347 --> 04:28.346
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

04:28.348 --> 04:30.214
MEANS YOUR AUNT BEV
IS FIGHTING.

04:30.216 --> 04:32.783
SHE'S GONNA BE BACK TO US
REAL SOON.

04:32.785 --> 04:34.618
HEY.

04:34.620 --> 04:36.987
I'M SORRY I SPENT THE NIGHT
LAST NIGHT. I DIDN'T MEAN TO.

04:36.989 --> 04:38.621
YOU CANNOT KEEP SLEEPING
IN THAT CHAIR.

04:38.623 --> 04:40.556
I KNOW.
IT'S JUST HARD LEAVING.

04:40.558 --> 04:42.958
YOU KNOW, I FEEL LIKE I SHOULD
BE HERE WHEN SHE WAKES UP.

04:42.960 --> 04:44.492
YOU'RE STILL RECOVERING. YOU GOT
TO TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF.

04:44.494 --> 04:45.593
I KNOW.

04:45.595 --> 04:47.528
OKAY.

04:47.530 --> 04:48.695
LET'S GET Y'ALL TO SCHOOL.

04:48.697 --> 04:50.463
BYE, AUNT BEV.
BYE.

04:50.465 --> 04:51.897
BYE, DAD. LOVE YOU.
BYE, GUYS. I LOVE YOU.

04:51.899 --> 04:53.431
TALK TO YOU LATER, BABE.
TALK TO YOU SOON.

05:01.306 --> 05:03.539
Noel:
LOOK, I GET THAT YOU'VE BEEN
HANDLING BUSINESS STUFF

05:03.541 --> 05:05.440
WHILE SCARLETT'S MOM'S
IN THE HOSPITAL,

05:05.442 --> 05:08.276
BUT THIS IS LIKE THE THIRD
BAND MEETING SHE'S MISSED.

05:08.278 --> 05:10.411
YOU GUYS GONNA BE READY
TO HIT THE ROAD IN A FEW WEEKS?

05:10.413 --> 05:13.881
I MEAN...IS EVERYTHING OKAY
WITH YOU TWO?

05:13.883 --> 05:15.682
WELL, YEAH, MAN.
OF COURSE IT IS.

05:15.684 --> 05:17.583
OKAY.

05:17.585 --> 05:19.952
SO WE GOOD TO GO
FOR THE SESSION TONIGHT?

05:19.954 --> 05:22.020
I KNOW IT'S LATE.
TRYING TO SQUEEZE IT IN.

05:22.022 --> 05:23.838
YEAH, YEAH.

05:23.839 --> 05:25.655
UH, WORKING AROUND
SCARLETT'S SCHEDULE, BUT, UH...

05:25.658 --> 05:26.990
ALL RIGHT.
...SHOULD BE.

05:26.992 --> 05:28.825
WE COULD ALWAYS
RECORD THE TRACKS SEPARATELY,

05:28.827 --> 05:30.026
LIKE EVERYONE ELSE
IN THIS TOWN.

05:30.028 --> 05:31.444
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:31.445 --> 05:32.861
NO, WE -- WE LIKE
RECORDING TOGETHER.

05:32.864 --> 05:35.397
THAT'S HOW
WE'VE ALWAYS DONE IT.

05:35.399 --> 05:37.732
OKAY. [ SIGHS ]

05:37.734 --> 05:39.567
THANKS, MAN.
SEE YOU TONIGHT.

05:43.673 --> 05:45.039
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

05:45.041 --> 05:46.306
[ SIGHS ]

05:46.308 --> 05:47.740
OKAY.

05:48.676 --> 05:52.677
[ RINGTONE PLAYS ]

05:52.679 --> 05:53.978
GUNNAR. HI.
HOW WAS THE MEETING?

05:53.980 --> 05:55.379
SORRY I COULDN'T MAKE IT.

05:55.381 --> 05:56.680
NO, NO. NO WORRIES.

05:56.682 --> 05:58.982
UM...
HOW'S YOUR MOM DOING?

05:58.984 --> 06:00.850
SHE'S AS GOOD
AS CAN BE EXPECTED.

06:00.852 --> 06:02.551
WELL, THAT'S --
THAT'S GOOD.

06:02.553 --> 06:03.818
UH [CHUCKLES] LOOK,

06:03.820 --> 06:05.986
I-I-I KNOW
WE HAVEN'T REALLY TALKED

06:05.988 --> 06:09.322
OR SEEN EACH OTHER
IN THE LAST FEW WEEKS,

06:09.324 --> 06:11.424
but we're supposed to
get together tonight

06:11.426 --> 06:13.759
AND RECORD FOR THE --
FOR THE E.P.

06:13.761 --> 06:15.026
I KNOW.

06:15.028 --> 06:16.827
Well, I was thinking
maybe we could, uh,

06:16.829 --> 06:19.029
COME AROUND HERE
A COUPLE HOURS BEFORE,

06:19.031 --> 06:20.363
UH, LISTEN TO THE TRACK,

06:20.365 --> 06:22.798
AND MAYBE, UH,
REHEARSE A LITTLE.

06:22.800 --> 06:23.999
YEAH, SURE.
THAT MAKES SENSE.

06:24.001 --> 06:25.567
I'LL, UM,
I'LL SEE YOU THEN.

06:25.569 --> 06:27.335
I'LL...SEE YOU THEN.

06:28.838 --> 06:30.437
WHO WAS THAT?

06:30.439 --> 06:31.971
GUNNAR.

06:31.973 --> 06:34.039
HAVEN'T SEEN MUCH OF HIM
LATELY.

06:34.041 --> 06:36.408
OR REALLY AT ALL,
I GUESS.

06:36.410 --> 06:38.309
WHAT IS THAT?

06:40.046 --> 06:43.013
THIS IS JUST
A LITTLE SOMETHING

06:43.015 --> 06:47.416
TO CELEBRATE
ONE MONTH OF LIVING TOGETHER.

06:47.418 --> 06:49.050
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:49.052 --> 06:50.051
THANK YOU.

06:50.053 --> 06:51.819
YEAH.
HOLD THIS.

06:55.591 --> 06:57.591
I KNOW
YOU LOVE VINTAGE.

06:57.593 --> 06:59.626
OH, IT IS GORGEOUS.

06:59.628 --> 07:01.661
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

07:01.663 --> 07:05.730
I JUST -- I REALLY WANTED TO SAY
THAT, UH...

07:05.732 --> 07:08.532
I LOVE...

07:08.534 --> 07:11.034
HAVING YOU HERE.

07:11.036 --> 07:14.337
AND I LOVE...

07:14.339 --> 07:15.504
BEING HERE.

07:17.374 --> 07:18.106
GOOD.

07:23.612 --> 07:24.945
Man:<i> ...WHOLE FAMILY.</i>

07:24.946 --> 07:26.279
MORNING, HONEY.
<i> ONE LUCKY VIEWER CAN ENTER</i>

07:26.280 --> 07:27.613
<i> TO WIN FREE TICKETS</i>
<i> ON OUR WEBSITE.</i>
MORNING.

07:27.616 --> 07:29.015
<i> GENERAL ADMISSION TICKETS...</i>

07:29.017 --> 07:31.017
AND GOOD MORNING,
SWEET PRINCESS.

07:31.019 --> 07:32.769
AWW.
<i>AND NOW FOR ENTERTAINMENT NEWS,</i>

07:32.770 --> 07:34.520
<i> IT WAS PREMIERE NIGHT</i>
<i> IN HOLLYWOOD LAST NIGHT...</i>

07:34.522 --> 07:35.654
I DIDN'T HEAR HER AT ALL
LAST NIGHT.

07:35.656 --> 07:37.389
YEAH,
SHE ONLY WOKE UP ONCE.

07:37.391 --> 07:38.790
A.J.:<i> JULIETTE,</i>
<i> YOU MUST BE SUPER-EXCITED --</i>

07:38.792 --> 07:39.924
<i> YOUR FIRST</i>
<i> HOLLYWOOD PREMIERE.</i>

07:39.926 --> 07:41.559
Carl: HEY,
HAVE YOU SEEN MY GLASSES?

07:41.560 --> 07:43.193
Juliette:<i> I AM.</i>
<i> IT'S A DREAM COME TRUE.</i>

07:43.194 --> 07:44.827
<i> AND THE REVIEWS, I SHOULD SAY,</i>
<i> HAVE BEEN FANTASTIC.</i>

07:44.830 --> 07:46.796
SON, STOP TORTURING YOURSELF,
HUH?

07:46.798 --> 07:48.464
<i> OF COURSE, THIS MOVIE</i>

07:48.466 --> 07:50.065
<i> ISN'T THE ONLY THING</i>
<i> YOU'VE GOT GOING ON.</i>

07:50.067 --> 07:51.833
<i> HOW IS THAT NEW BABY</i>
<i> OF YOURS DOING?</i>

07:51.835 --> 07:53.568
<i> SHE'S SO GOOD.</i>

07:53.570 --> 07:55.703
<i> SHE'S AT HOME WITH MY</i>
<i> INCREDIBLY SUPPORTIVE HUSBAND.</i>

07:55.705 --> 07:56.937
WHILE YOU PARADE
AROUND HOLLYWOOD,

07:56.939 --> 07:58.505
AVOIDING
YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES.

07:58.507 --> 07:59.639
[ TV SHUTS OFF ]

07:59.641 --> 08:00.940
WELL, SON,
SHE WAS ALWAYS A LONG SHOT.

08:00.942 --> 08:04.742
DAD, JUST...
SAY NOTHING, OKAY?

08:04.744 --> 08:06.844
[ SIGHS ]

08:08.581 --> 08:09.746
HAVE YOU HEARD ANYTHING
FROM HER?

08:11.449 --> 08:12.915
HAVE YOU REACHED OUT
TO HER?

08:12.917 --> 08:16.651
SHE'S THE ONE
WHO SAID SHE DOESN'T NEED US.

08:16.653 --> 08:18.586
WELL, MAYBE YOU<i> SHOULD.</i>

08:18.588 --> 08:19.987
SHE DID MENTION YOU.

08:19.989 --> 08:22.122
[ SCOFFS ]

08:22.124 --> 08:25.058
[ BATTLE TAPES' "FEEL THE SAME"
PLAYS ]

08:25.060 --> 08:28.961
Man:
HEY, CAN WE GET SOME BREAKFAST
FROM ROOM SERVICE OR SOMETHING?

08:28.963 --> 08:31.930
TEQUILA SHOT,
OR DO YOU WANT VODKA?

08:34.834 --> 08:36.967
[ VOMITING ]

08:36.969 --> 08:39.002
[ COUGHING ]

08:46.678 --> 08:49.612
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

08:58.122 --> 09:00.388
WHEELIN' DEALIN' RECEIVES
ALL RIGHTS TO HER NEW ALBUM,

09:00.390 --> 09:03.124
PLUS THAT BUYS OUT HER OPTIONS
FOR TWO FOLLOW-UP ALBUMS.

09:03.126 --> 09:04.792
LAWYERS ARE HAPPY.
IT'S A GOOD DEAL.

09:04.794 --> 09:06.160
DAMN STRAIGHT IT IS.

09:06.162 --> 09:08.795
HIGHWAY 65
IS GONNA END UP

09:08.797 --> 09:10.930
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]
WITH A LOT OF MONEY
FROM THIS DEAL.

09:10.932 --> 09:12.164
[ SCOFFS ]

09:12.166 --> 09:13.532
JULIETTE.

09:13.534 --> 09:14.633
[ LAUGHS ]

09:14.635 --> 09:15.967
GOOD TIMING, GIRL.

09:15.969 --> 09:17.201
KIND OF EARLY OUT WEST,
ISN'T IT?

09:17.203 --> 09:18.468
HI, JULIETTE.

09:18.470 --> 09:21.204
[ CRYING ]

09:21.206 --> 09:22.905
JULIETTE?

09:26.210 --> 09:29.544
[ Crying ]
RAYNA, I...

09:29.546 --> 09:31.979
I CAN'T...

09:31.981 --> 09:33.480
YOU CAN'T WHAT?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

09:33.482 --> 09:35.515
PLEASE...I NEED...

09:35.517 --> 09:36.916
YOU NEED HELP?
WHERE ARE YOU?

09:36.918 --> 09:38.183
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
Woman: HEY, JULIETTE.

09:38.185 --> 09:40.151
WE'RE ORDERING BREAKFAST
FROM ROOM SERVICE.

09:40.153 --> 09:41.452
WANT ANYTHING?

09:41.454 --> 09:43.654
Juliette?

09:43.656 --> 09:46.223
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

09:46.225 --> 09:47.757
WHAT WAS THAT?

09:47.759 --> 09:50.693
I DON'T KNOW.

09:50.695 --> 09:52.661
SOMETHING IS
REALLY, REALLY WRONG.

09:52.663 --> 09:57.732
¶¶

10:04.206 --> 10:05.772
[ GROANS ]

10:05.774 --> 10:07.106
Kevin:
I GOT TO GO TO WORK,

10:07.108 --> 10:08.841
BUT I WAS WONDERING
ABOUT<i> YOUR</i> SCHEDULE.

10:08.843 --> 10:10.475
YOU STAYING IN BED AGAIN,
OR IS THIS THE DAY

10:10.477 --> 10:12.877
YOU FINALLY GO OUT AND DO
PRETTY MUCH ANYTHING ELSE?

10:12.879 --> 10:14.044
I WENT TO GUNNAR'S.

10:14.046 --> 10:15.645
THAT WAS THREE DAYS AGO.

10:15.647 --> 10:16.979
AND GOING TO YOUR HOUSE
TO GET CLEAN CLOTHES

10:16.981 --> 10:18.213
DOESN'T COUNT
AS DOING SOMETHING.

10:18.215 --> 10:20.114
THIS ISN'T MY CALL.

10:21.250 --> 10:23.950
LUKE PUT ME IN A HOLDING PATTERN
AFTER THE PRESS CONFERENCE.

10:23.952 --> 10:25.985
I CAN'T WORK ON MY ALBUM.
I CAN'T TOUR.

10:25.987 --> 10:27.219
IT DOESN'T MEAN
YOU CAN'T KEEP WRITING.

10:27.221 --> 10:29.254
YOU HAVEN'T EVEN TOUCHED
YOUR GUITAR.

10:29.256 --> 10:31.990
WELL, I'M NOT REALLY
FEELING IT RIGHT NOW.

10:31.992 --> 10:34.492
WELL, I'M NOT REALLY FEELING
ANOTHER NIGHT

10:34.494 --> 10:36.093
LOCKED IN THIS BEDROOM,
WATCHING TV.

10:37.830 --> 10:40.063
THEN I GUESS
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

10:42.200 --> 10:44.066
[ SIGHS ]

10:44.068 --> 10:49.704
¶ YOU SHOULD KNOW
THERE WILL BE DAYS ¶

10:49.706 --> 10:55.575
¶ WHEN YOU PRAY FOR SUN
BUT GET THE RAIN ¶

10:55.577 --> 11:02.181
¶ WHEN THE TEARS FALL DOWN
YOUR PRETTY FACE ¶

11:02.183 --> 11:07.686
¶ MY LOVE
WILL BLOW THE STORM AWAY ¶

11:08.989 --> 11:15.025
¶ LIFE IS FULL
OF UPS AND DOWNS ¶

11:15.027 --> 11:20.996
¶ AND I CAN'T
CHANGE THE WORLD AROUND ¶

11:20.998 --> 11:26.601
¶ THE ONLY THING THAT I CAN DO ¶

11:30.006 --> 11:35.809
¶ IS ALWAYS KEEP ON LOVING YOU ¶

11:37.813 --> 11:39.579
HOW'S SHE DOING?

11:40.782 --> 11:41.947
SHE'S GONNA WAKE UP
ANY MINUTE.

11:41.949 --> 11:43.782
[ CHUCKLES ]
I KNOW IT.

11:43.784 --> 11:45.683
WHAT ABOUT<i> YOU?</i>

11:45.685 --> 11:46.950
HOW LONG YOU BEEN HERE?

11:49.321 --> 11:50.720
DEACON.

11:50.722 --> 11:51.971
HEY, LOOK,
IT'S MY FAULT,

11:51.972 --> 11:53.221
AND I FIGURE
THIS IS THE LEAST I CAN DO.

11:53.224 --> 11:54.607
I'M THE ONE WHO ASKED HER
TO COME HERE IN THE FIRST PLACE.

11:54.608 --> 11:55.991
SCARLETT, COME ON, NOW.
THAT'S NOT WHY SHE'S HERE.

11:55.993 --> 11:57.792
WE NEED TO STOP.

11:57.794 --> 11:59.026
SHE HAD AN ANEURYSM.

11:59.028 --> 12:00.694
SHE DIDN'T TELL ANYBODY

12:00.696 --> 12:03.163
SHE WAS TAKING SUPPLEMENTS
FOR MENOPAUSE,

12:03.165 --> 12:05.665
SO HER BLOOD WAS THIN
AND THE BLEED WAS WORSE.

12:05.667 --> 12:06.966
THAT'S ON<i> HER --</i>

12:06.968 --> 12:08.867
NOT YOU,
NOT YOUR LIVER TRANSPLANT.

12:08.869 --> 12:10.101
SHE WOULDN'T BE HERE
IF IT WASN'T --

12:10.103 --> 12:11.602
THIS WAS HER CHOICE.

12:11.604 --> 12:13.270
[ SIGHS ]

12:13.272 --> 12:14.771
DON'T MAKE HER HAVE MADE
THAT CHOICE FOR NOTHING

12:14.773 --> 12:16.272
BY NOT LIVING
THE LIFE SHE GAVE YOU.

12:21.111 --> 12:22.643
[ SMOOCHES ]

12:24.680 --> 12:26.579
I'LL GET YOU
SOME COFFEE.

12:30.050 --> 12:31.649
[ SIGHS ]

12:31.651 --> 12:33.584
Layla: I NEED TO REMEMBER
TO KEEP MY HAND ON MY HIP.

12:33.586 --> 12:35.018
IT LOOKS BETTER THAT WAY.

12:35.020 --> 12:36.586
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

12:36.588 --> 12:38.654
IT'S ALWAYS BETTER
WHEN YOU'RE HERE TO REMIND ME.

12:38.656 --> 12:40.122
Patrick: HEY, LAYLA.
YOU IN THERE?

12:40.124 --> 12:41.123
I MISS YOU.

12:41.125 --> 12:43.158
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

12:43.160 --> 12:45.360
YEAH.
I THINK PATRICK'S HERE.

12:45.362 --> 12:46.761
ALL RIGHT, FINE.

12:46.763 --> 12:49.096
JEFF WANTS
TO TALK TO YOU.

12:49.098 --> 12:50.697
HEY.

12:50.699 --> 12:52.123
HEY, YOU KNOW,
THERE ARE NO PICTURES...
YEAH.

12:52.124 --> 12:53.548
...OF ME AND JULIETTE
TOGETHER.
YEAH, OKAY.

12:53.549 --> 12:54.973
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
MAYBE WE COULD GET SOME

12:54.974 --> 12:56.398
AT THE CONCERT
OR THE AFTER PARTY TONIGHT.
UH-HUH. MM-HMM.

12:56.403 --> 12:58.369
I STAND A BETTER CHANCE
OF GETTING ANY PRES...
GREAT. SOUNDS GOOD.

12:58.371 --> 12:59.169
...IF I'M WITH HER.

12:59.171 --> 13:00.370
GOT IT.

13:00.372 --> 13:02.271
YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO THE CONCERT.

13:02.273 --> 13:03.622
I'M NOT?

13:03.623 --> 13:04.972
JEFF JUST TALKED
TO HIS FRIEND VALERIE,

13:04.975 --> 13:07.275
THE CASTING DIRECTOR
FOR THE PATSY CLINE MOVIE.

13:07.277 --> 13:10.611
YOU'RE HAVING DINNER WITH HER
AND HER PRODUCER TONIGHT.

13:10.613 --> 13:11.912
HE SAYS THAT SHE REMEMBERS
YOUR AUDITION --

13:11.914 --> 13:14.381
THINKS YOU MIGHT HAVE
A VERY BRIGHT FUTURE.

13:14.383 --> 13:15.982
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

13:15.984 --> 13:17.817
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:17.819 --> 13:19.285
OH, MY GOD.

13:19.287 --> 13:21.120
[ Chuckling ]
OH, MY GOD!

13:21.122 --> 13:23.755
YOU'RE THE BEST, JEFF.

13:23.757 --> 13:25.223
OKAY.

13:25.225 --> 13:26.624
YEAH.

13:26.626 --> 13:28.892
UM,
I NEED TO GO SHOPPING.

13:28.894 --> 13:31.160
I'M MEETING A PRODUCER.
I'VE GOT TO WEAR SOMETHING NICE.

13:31.162 --> 13:32.628
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

13:32.630 --> 13:34.229
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:34.231 --> 13:36.931
WOW.
SHE BOUGHT IT.

13:36.933 --> 13:39.233
SO, ARE YOU GONNA SET THAT
MEETING WITH VALERIE, OR AM<i> I?</i>

13:39.235 --> 13:40.968
HEY.

13:40.970 --> 13:42.069
HI.

13:42.071 --> 13:44.137
I WAS EXPECTING SCARLETT
AND COFFEE.

13:44.139 --> 13:45.805
WELL,
YOU GOT ME AND NOTHING.

13:45.807 --> 13:47.173
[ CHUCKLES ]
I'LL TAKE IT.

13:47.175 --> 13:48.807
MM.
HOW YOU DOING, BABE?

13:48.809 --> 13:50.175
I'M GOOD, YEAH.
COME ON. SIT DOWN.

13:50.177 --> 13:51.376
NO, NO, NO.
DON'T DO THAT.

13:51.378 --> 13:52.643
I CAN MOVE A CHAIR.
COME ON.

13:52.645 --> 13:54.344
YES, I CAN.

13:54.346 --> 13:57.347
WHAT'S GOING ON?

13:57.349 --> 14:01.350
WELL, I SIGNED THE CONTRACT
RELEASING JULIETTE TODAY.

14:01.352 --> 14:03.218
WELL, GOOD.
THAT'S GOOD, RIGHT?

14:03.220 --> 14:04.786
YEP.

14:04.788 --> 14:06.821
RIGHT AFTERWARDS,
I GOT A PHONE CALL FROM HER,

14:06.823 --> 14:09.423
AND SHE WAS...
[ SIGHS ]

14:09.425 --> 14:12.659
CRYING AND UNINTELLIGIBLE.

14:12.661 --> 14:15.261
THAT'S OFFICIALLY NOT
YOUR PROBLEM ANYMORE, RIGHT?
NO, IT'S NOT.

14:15.263 --> 14:17.696
I CAN'T HELP BUT WORRY ABOUT HER
A LITTLE BIT, THOUGH.

14:17.698 --> 14:21.299
I MEAN, SHE HAD
TERRIBLE POSTPARTUM DEPRESSION,

14:21.301 --> 14:23.868
AND NOW EVERYBODY'S SAYING
SHE'S OUT PARTYING EVERY NIGHT.

14:23.870 --> 14:25.936
YOU BEEN IN TOUCH
WITH HER PEOPLE?

14:25.938 --> 14:27.538
AVERY?

14:27.539 --> 14:29.139
APPARENTLY,
AVERY'S MOVED BACK TO OHIO,

14:29.141 --> 14:30.791
WHICH CAN'T BE GOOD.

14:30.792 --> 14:32.442
YOU KNOW, SHE'S LEFT GLENN,
SIGNED WITH JEFF FORDHAM.

14:32.444 --> 14:33.943
OH, GOD.

14:33.945 --> 14:35.244
TRIED TO CALL HIM,
TRIED CALLING LUKE.

14:35.246 --> 14:36.878
NOBODY'S RETURNING
MY PHONE CALLS.

14:36.880 --> 14:38.212
SWEAR I FEEL LIKE
I NEED TO JUST PICK UP

14:38.214 --> 14:39.346
AND GO TALK TO HER.

14:39.348 --> 14:40.664
I THINK
YOU'RE PROBABLY RIGHT.

14:40.665 --> 14:41.981
YOU SHOULD GO OUT THERE
AND SEE WHAT YOU CAN DO.

14:41.983 --> 14:43.248
YEAH, BUT I DON'T WANT
TO LEAVE YOU.

14:43.250 --> 14:44.633
I'M NOT GONNA LEAVE
THE GIRLS.

14:44.634 --> 14:46.017
COME ON, NOW. YOU'VE BEEN
DOING EVERYTHING HERE.

14:46.019 --> 14:47.451
YOU'VE BEEN RUNNING
THE KIDS EVERYPLACE

14:47.453 --> 14:48.885
AND TAKING ME
TO PHYSICAL THERAPY,

14:48.887 --> 14:50.219
COMING BACK AND FORTH
TO HERE.

14:50.221 --> 14:52.154
I'M FEELING BETTER.
SHE'S DOING BETTER.

14:52.156 --> 14:54.723
I CAN TAKE ONE NIGHT OFF
AND TAKE CARE OF THE GIRLS

14:54.725 --> 14:56.825
SO YOU CAN GO AND DO
WHAT YOU GOT TO DO.

14:59.863 --> 15:03.130
OKAY, WHATEVER, MOM.
HAVE FUN.

15:03.132 --> 15:04.831
I CAN'T BELIEVE SHE WON'T
TAKE US TO L.A. WITH HER.

15:04.833 --> 15:06.132
IT'S FOR ONE NIGHT.

15:06.134 --> 15:08.968
WE GOT LETTERS
FROM DAD.

15:08.970 --> 15:10.869
OH. REALLY?

15:10.871 --> 15:12.704
HERE'S ONE FOR YOU.

15:16.209 --> 15:17.441
AREN'T YOU GONNA
OPEN YOURS?

15:22.180 --> 15:23.412
WHY WOULD YOU DO THAT?!

15:24.848 --> 15:26.414
BECAUSE IT'LL JUST SAY
THE SAME THING

15:26.416 --> 15:27.748
AS THE LAST THREE
HE ALREADY SENT --

15:27.750 --> 15:29.316
"I'M SORRY.
I LOVE YOU."

15:29.318 --> 15:30.283
WHATEVER.

15:37.391 --> 15:40.358
NOW KEVIN'S ACTING
LIKE IT'S ALL ME.

15:40.360 --> 15:43.127
I MEAN, IT'S NOT<i> MY</i> FAULT LUKE
TOLD ME NOT TO GO OUT IN PUBLIC.

15:43.129 --> 15:44.461
OKAY.

15:44.463 --> 15:47.197
SLIGHT --
<i> MAJOR</i> EXAGGERATION THERE.

15:47.199 --> 15:49.265
LUKE PULLED YOU OFF HIS TOUR
TEMPORARILY AND ASKED YOU

15:49.267 --> 15:51.133
TO RUN ANY PRESS REQUESTS
THROUGH HIM AND JIMMY.

15:51.135 --> 15:52.767
I DON'T WANT TO DO
ANY PRESS.

15:52.769 --> 15:54.235
WELL, GREAT.
IT'S A WIN/WIN.

15:54.237 --> 15:55.737
I DON'T GET IT, MAN.

15:55.738 --> 15:57.238
WHY'D YOU COME OUT
JUST SO YOU COULD STAY IN?

15:57.240 --> 15:59.506
SEEMS LIKE YOU TOOK
A HUGE LEAP FOR NOTHING.

15:59.508 --> 16:02.108
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT I'M GOING THROUGH.

16:02.110 --> 16:04.743
OKAY. YEAH.

16:04.745 --> 16:06.111
BUT<i> KEVIN</i> DOES.

16:06.113 --> 16:07.946
AND IT SEEMS LIKE
HE'S BEEN PRETTY DAMN PATIENT,

16:07.948 --> 16:09.915
IF YOU ASK ME.

16:09.916 --> 16:11.883
I MEAN, WHEN'S THE LAST TIME
YOU GUYS EVEN WENT OUT?

16:11.885 --> 16:13.317
LOOK, AT SOME POINT,
YOU JUST GOT TO STOP

16:13.319 --> 16:16.286
BEING AFRAID OF WHO YOU ARE NOW
AND -- AND...

16:16.288 --> 16:19.421
TRUST THAT WHAT'S MEANT TO BE
IS MEANT TO BE.

16:20.490 --> 16:21.856
OR AT LEAST
TAKE A SHOWER.

16:39.975 --> 16:41.874
[ SIGHS ]

17:05.032 --> 17:06.865
I HEARD THERE'S
THIS NEW CLUB DOWNTOWN

17:06.867 --> 17:09.000
THAT'S SUPPOSED TO BE
OFF THE HOOK!

17:09.002 --> 17:10.201
I'LL CALL AND TELL THEM
<i> YOU</i> WANT TO COME,

17:10.203 --> 17:11.202
AND THEN
WE'LL DEFINITELY GET IN.

17:11.204 --> 17:13.404
WHATEVER.

17:13.406 --> 17:14.872
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]
I'M TOTALLY
GONNA WEAR THIS TONIGHT.

17:14.874 --> 17:17.207
OH, MY GOSH.
I'M GONNA LOOK SO CUTE!

17:17.209 --> 17:19.075
IS THAT CHRIS PRATT?

17:19.077 --> 17:20.810
IS HE COMING
TO THE AFTER PARTY TONIGHT?

17:20.812 --> 17:22.511
IT'S NOBODY.

17:28.818 --> 17:30.450
Man:
<i> LADIES AND GENTLEMEN...</i>

17:30.452 --> 17:31.951
NO LAYLA TONIGHT?

17:31.953 --> 17:33.519
JEFF WANTED THE FOCUS
TO BE ALL ON YOU --

17:33.521 --> 17:34.820
RIGHT WHERE IT SHOULD BE.

17:34.822 --> 17:36.021
DAMN STRAIGHT.

17:36.023 --> 17:37.222
KICK ASS TONIGHT.

17:37.224 --> 17:38.256
I ALWAYS DO.

17:38.258 --> 17:39.357
<i> ...JULIETTE BARNES!</i>

17:39.359 --> 17:40.524
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

17:40.526 --> 17:42.392
WHAT'S UP, LOS ANGELES?

17:57.041 --> 17:58.873
YOU WANT TO TALK
ABOUT IT?

18:01.611 --> 18:02.977
[ SIGHS ]
I JUST KEEP THINKING

18:02.979 --> 18:07.014
THAT SHE'S GONNA CALL
OR TEXT OR WHATEVER,

18:07.016 --> 18:09.049
BUT SHE HASN'T.

18:09.051 --> 18:12.419
AND I CAN'T GO ANYWHERE
WITHOUT SEEING PICTURES OF HER,

18:12.421 --> 18:15.422
LOOKING LIKE
HER LIFE IS PERFECT.

18:15.424 --> 18:16.890
MAYBE IT IS.

18:16.892 --> 18:19.158
MAYBE SHE'S HAPPIER
WITHOUT US.

18:19.160 --> 18:22.194
SO WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?
YOU DONE WITH THIS MARRIAGE?

18:22.196 --> 18:24.062
NO. THAT'S NOT
WHAT I'M SAYING.

18:24.064 --> 18:26.030
I MEAN,
I TAKE MY VOWS SERIOUSLY.

18:26.032 --> 18:28.465
YOU TOOK A VOW TO BE A HUSBAND,
NOT A MARTYR.

18:28.467 --> 18:31.634
AND YOU CAN'T BE A HUSBAND
TO SOMEONE WHO'S NOT THERE.

18:31.636 --> 18:34.336
SWEETHEART, I WILL SUPPORT YOU
NO MATTER WHAT YOU DECIDE TO DO,

18:34.338 --> 18:36.538
BUT EVENTUALLY, YOU'RE GOING TO
HAVE TO ACTUALLY DO SOMETHING.

18:36.540 --> 18:39.374
WHY DON'T YOU STAY?

18:39.376 --> 18:41.175
HERE?

18:41.177 --> 18:42.409
WHY NOT?

18:42.411 --> 18:43.877
YOU'D HAVE FAMILY HERE

18:43.879 --> 18:45.645
TO HELP YOU TAKE CARE
OF THAT LITTLE GIRL --

18:45.647 --> 18:48.314
PEOPLE THAT LOVE HER,
PEOPLE THAT LOVE<i> YOU,</i>

18:48.316 --> 18:52.284
PEOPLE WHO ACTUALLY CARE
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENS TO YOU.

18:52.286 --> 18:54.185
LOOK, I CAN MAKE SOME CALLS
ABOUT A JOB.

18:54.187 --> 18:56.053
YOUR MOM AND I
CAN HELP YOU GET STARTED.

18:56.055 --> 18:58.121
I KNOW IT MAY NOT BE
A GLAMOROUS LIFE,

18:58.123 --> 18:59.622
BUT IT'S A GOOD ONE.

18:59.624 --> 19:01.657
YOU TURNED OUT
PRETTY WELL.

19:03.093 --> 19:04.559
[ CROWD CHEERING ]

19:04.561 --> 19:07.628
Juliette:
¶ I'M NOT TWISTED, BITTER,
I'M NOT MAD ¶

19:07.630 --> 19:09.463
Luke:
[ Chuckling ] HEY!
HEY!

19:09.465 --> 19:11.598
HEY, MAN, I APPRECIATE
YOU COMING OUT TO DO THIS.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

19:11.600 --> 19:13.199
JULIETTE'S A HUGE FAN.

19:13.201 --> 19:14.967
THIS IS A BIG BUCKET-LIST THING
FOR HER TO MEET YOU.

19:14.969 --> 19:17.369
HER NEW SINGLE --
OVER THE MOON.

19:17.371 --> 19:19.471
OH, WELL,<i> YOUR</i> NEW SINGLE
IS OVER THE MOON. IT'S AWESOME.

19:19.473 --> 19:21.239
WHY, THANK YOU KINDLY.

19:21.241 --> 19:23.207
HEARD IT FIRST TIME
TWO YEARS AGO AT THE BLUEBIRD.

19:23.209 --> 19:25.676
WE RECORDED IT, AND I THINK
IT'S GONNA BE AN H-I-T.

19:25.678 --> 19:27.094
I THINK IT IS, TOO.

19:27.095 --> 19:28.511
BUT DON'T HOLD ME TO IT.
S.T., WE GOT TO GO.

19:28.514 --> 19:29.479
OKAY.
ALL RIGHT, BROTHER.

19:29.481 --> 19:30.580
HEY, I'LL SEE YOU
IN A MINUTE.

19:30.582 --> 19:31.980
YOU TAKE CARE.
OKAY.

19:34.017 --> 19:35.249
RAYNA.

19:35.251 --> 19:36.950
HI.
HEY.

19:36.952 --> 19:38.651
NICE OF S.T.
TO SHOW UP FOR YA.
YEAH.

19:38.653 --> 19:41.153
NO DIFFERENCE BETWEEN COUNTRY
AND ROCK 'N' ROLL ANYMORE, HUH?

19:41.155 --> 19:42.588
THAT MIGHT BE TRUE.

19:42.589 --> 19:44.022
WHAT IN THE WORLD
ARE YOU DOING OUT HERE?

19:44.024 --> 19:45.557
I THOUGHT THE DAYS

19:45.558 --> 19:47.091
OF YOU FLYING CROSS-COUNTRY
TO SEE ME WERE OVER.

19:47.093 --> 19:48.125
THEY ARE.

19:48.127 --> 19:49.360
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

19:49.361 --> 19:50.594
AND IF YOU'D
HAVE CALLED ME BACK,

19:50.596 --> 19:51.928
YOU MIGHT'VE SAVED ME
A TRIP.

19:51.930 --> 19:53.562
YOU CAME 'CAUSE
I DIDN'T CALL YOU BACK?

19:53.564 --> 19:56.131
NO, I CAME
'CAUSE JULIETTE CALLED ME.

19:56.133 --> 19:58.133
REALLY?
MM-HMM.

19:58.135 --> 19:59.300
AND WHY WOULD SHE DO THAT?

19:59.302 --> 20:00.534
I DON'T KNOW.
HOW'S SHE DOING?

20:00.536 --> 20:02.202
SHE'S GOOD.
WE'RE HAVING A GREAT TIME.

20:02.204 --> 20:03.436
MM-HMM.

20:03.438 --> 20:04.670
WHAT?

20:04.672 --> 20:06.038
Y'ALL HAVEN'T HAD
A NIGHT OFF

20:06.040 --> 20:08.473
SINCE YOU LEFT NASHVILLE
OVER A MONTH AGO.

20:08.475 --> 20:10.441
IN THAT TIME, HOW OFTEN
HAS SHE SEEN HER HUSBAND

20:10.443 --> 20:12.342
AND HER NEWBORN BABY?

20:12.344 --> 20:16.212
SEE, NOW, IF IT'S<i> ME,</i>
I'D BE WORRIED ABOUT THAT.

20:16.214 --> 20:19.315
¶ ...MISSISSIPPI FLOOD,
THIS LOVE... ¶

20:28.258 --> 20:30.157
[ SIGHS ]

20:38.600 --> 20:41.434
[ DOOR OPENS ]

20:41.436 --> 20:42.334
HEY.

20:42.336 --> 20:44.669
HEY.

20:44.671 --> 20:46.137
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

20:46.139 --> 20:47.471
IT'S BEEN A WHILE.

20:47.473 --> 20:50.474
YEAH, IT'S BEEN
LIKE A MONTH SINCE...

20:50.476 --> 20:52.476
ALL THAT STUFF HAPPENED
WITH MY MOM.

20:52.478 --> 20:53.977
YEAH.
[ Chuckling ] HEY.

20:58.450 --> 21:00.082
YOU KNOW, I, UH,

21:00.084 --> 21:02.584
I CANCELED MY TRIP TO TEXAS,
UH, TO SEE KILEY,

21:02.586 --> 21:04.218
JUST IN CASE
YOU NEEDED ANYTHING,

21:04.220 --> 21:05.986
BUT YOU NEVER, UH...

21:05.988 --> 21:08.588
OH, WELL, I HAVE
SO MUCH SUPPORT ALREADY,

21:08.590 --> 21:10.256
AND, UM, I DIDN'T WANT
TO BE A BURDEN TO YOU.

21:10.258 --> 21:11.023
THANK YOU, THOUGH.

21:11.025 --> 21:12.391
YEAH.

21:12.393 --> 21:14.426
YOU KNOW,
I WAS KIND OF WONDERING

21:14.427 --> 21:16.460
IF IT HAD ANYTHING TO DO
WITH WHAT HAPPENED ON THE ROOF.

21:16.463 --> 21:18.696
I THOUGHT MAYBE
WE SHOULD TALK ABOUT THAT.

21:21.400 --> 21:22.766
BUT NOTHING HAPPENED
UP ON THE ROOF.

21:22.767 --> 21:24.133
THAT WAS A WEIRD NIGHT,
BETWEEN MY MAMA AND DEACON.

21:24.136 --> 21:26.269
DON'T REALLY NEED
TO RELIVE IT, SO...

21:26.271 --> 21:29.005
BUT WE COULD GET STARTED
ON THESE HARMONIES.

21:29.007 --> 21:31.007
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
SURE, SURE.

21:31.008 --> 21:33.008
I, UH, GOT A BASIC
GUITAR TRACK LAID DOWN,

21:33.011 --> 21:35.211
SO WE CAN JUST SING
ON TOP OF THAT.

21:35.213 --> 21:36.445
COOL.

21:36.447 --> 21:37.712
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

21:41.384 --> 21:44.451
¶ I'M CRAZY ¶

21:44.453 --> 21:46.519
¶ OOH, OOH, OOH ¶

21:46.521 --> 21:52.357
¶ CRAZY FOR FEELIN' SO LONELY ¶

21:52.359 --> 21:54.459
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

21:54.461 --> 21:57.294
¶ I'M CRAZY ¶

21:58.597 --> 22:05.201
¶ CRAZY FOR FEELIN' BLUE ¶

22:05.203 --> 22:06.769
MM. I JUST LOVE HER.

22:06.771 --> 22:08.370
ISN'T SHE JUST
THE BEST OF THE BEST?

22:08.372 --> 22:09.804
¶ I KNEW ¶

22:09.806 --> 22:11.438
¶ OOH, OOH, OOH ¶
YEP.

22:11.440 --> 22:12.639
ARE YOU AND JULIETTE
FRIENDS?

22:12.641 --> 22:15.675
¶ YOU'D LOVE ME
AS LONG AS YOU WANTED ¶

22:15.677 --> 22:17.143
YES.

22:17.145 --> 22:19.445
[ CHUCKLES ]
THAT'S COOL.

22:19.447 --> 22:21.113
OLD FRIENDS ARE COOL.

22:21.115 --> 22:23.682
I'M HER BEST FRIEND.
¶ AND THEN SOMEDAY ¶

22:23.684 --> 22:28.452
¶ YOU'D LEAVE ME
FOR SOMEBODY NEW ¶

22:28.454 --> 22:30.619
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

22:33.256 --> 22:36.257
¶ WORRY ¶

22:36.259 --> 22:42.329
¶ WHY DO I LET MYSELF WORRY? ¶

22:44.066 --> 22:45.565
¶ OOH, OOH ¶

22:45.567 --> 22:48.801
¶ WONDERIN' ¶

22:48.803 --> 22:54.406
¶ WHAT IN THE WORLD
DID I DO? ¶

22:54.408 --> 22:58.076
¶ OOH, OOH, OOH ¶

22:58.078 --> 23:00.812
¶ CRAZY ¶

23:00.814 --> 23:08.419
¶ FOR THINKIN' THAT MY LOVE
COULD HOLD YOOOOOOOOOU ¶

23:08.421 --> 23:09.686
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

23:09.688 --> 23:13.556
¶ YEAH,
I'M CRAZY FOR TRYIN' ¶

23:13.558 --> 23:16.458
¶ AND CRAZY FOR CRYIN' ¶

23:16.460 --> 23:19.327
¶ AND I'M CRAZY ¶

23:19.329 --> 23:25.599
¶ FOR LOVIN' ¶

23:25.601 --> 23:30.536
¶ YOOOOOOOOOOOOOOU ¶

23:30.538 --> 23:33.338
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

23:46.119 --> 23:47.818
BEVERLY.

23:49.288 --> 23:50.687
UH, HELLO?!

23:50.689 --> 23:52.388
HELLO?! COULD SOMEBODY
COME IN HERE, PLEASE?!

23:53.824 --> 23:55.757
SHE SQUEEZED MY HAND.
SHE SQUEEZED MY HAND LIKE TWICE.

23:55.759 --> 23:57.458
I'LL GET THE DOCTOR.
BEVERLY.

23:57.460 --> 23:59.259
[ SIGHS ]

23:59.261 --> 24:00.860
THANK YOU, LORD.

24:00.862 --> 24:03.162
OH, MY GOD.
THANK YOU.

24:03.164 --> 24:05.597
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:08.134 --> 24:09.800
[ CRYING ]

24:17.776 --> 24:20.576
[<i> GUITAR PLAYING</i> ]
¶ IT WASN'T ONE BIG BLOW
THAT BROUGHT OUR LOVE DOWN ¶

24:22.346 --> 24:26.413
¶ IT WAS THE HAIRLINE CRACKS
THAT TOOK IT TO THE GROUND ¶

24:28.316 --> 24:31.917
¶ JUST KEPT CREEPIN'
OVER TIME ¶

24:31.919 --> 24:34.753
¶ SPREADIN'
LIKE WILDFIRE ¶

24:34.755 --> 24:38.890
¶ IT WASN'T ONE BIG BLOW
THAT BROUGHT OUR LOVE DOWN ¶

24:41.661 --> 24:46.330
¶ OOH,
YOU DIDN'T WANT TO SEE ¶

24:46.332 --> 24:48.799
¶ DIDN'T WANT TO BELIEVE ¶

24:48.801 --> 24:52.234
¶ THE DREAMS GETTING COLDER ¶

24:53.837 --> 24:58.272
¶ OOH, WE BEGGED THE TRUTH
TO BEND ¶

24:58.274 --> 25:01.608
¶ IT'S EASIER TO PRETEND ¶

25:01.610 --> 25:06.212
¶ THAN TO SEE
WHEN YOU'RE SOBER ¶

25:06.214 --> 25:07.680
¶ YEAH ¶

25:07.682 --> 25:10.949
¶ YOU ONLY WAKE UP
WHEN IT'S OVER ¶

25:13.553 --> 25:18.321
¶ YOU ONLY WAKE UP
WHEN IT'S OVER ¶

25:18.323 --> 25:22.491
¶ THERE WAS SO MUCH 'BOUT YOU
I DIDN'T REALIZE ¶

25:24.795 --> 25:29.263
¶ THERE WAS SO MUCH 'BOUT ME
I COULDN'T RECOGNIZE ¶

25:30.566 --> 25:34.333
¶ 'CAUSE YOU CAN ONLY
GET A CLEAR VIEW ¶

25:34.335 --> 25:37.235
¶ WHEN IT'S FADIN' IN THE WIND ¶

25:37.237 --> 25:40.871
¶ THERE WAS SO MUCH 'BOUT YOU
I DIDN'T REALIZE ¶

25:43.709 --> 25:45.709
[<i> MUSIC CONTINUES</i> ]

26:00.992 --> 26:02.891
STOP!

26:02.893 --> 26:04.525
STOP.

26:04.527 --> 26:06.393
WE CAN'T.
WE...CAN'T.

26:07.863 --> 26:09.696
SCARLETT.

26:09.698 --> 26:11.998
I'M SO VULNERABLE
AT THE MOMENT.

26:12.000 --> 26:13.599
I NEED YOU TO NOT DO THAT,
PLEASE.

26:13.601 --> 26:15.367
YOU CAN'T PUT THIS
ALL ON ME, SCARLETT.

26:15.369 --> 26:16.568
YOU WERE
KISSING ME BACK, TOO,

26:16.570 --> 26:18.002
LIKE YOU WANTED TO KISS ME
UP ON THAT ROOF.

26:18.004 --> 26:19.336
I DIDN'T WANT TO KISS YOU
ON THE ROOF, GUNNAR.

26:19.338 --> 26:20.504
YOU IGNORED ME
FOR A MONTH,

26:20.505 --> 26:21.671
THINKING THIS WAS
JUST GONNA GO AWAY,

26:21.673 --> 26:23.906
BUT IT'S NOT,
BECAUSE IT IS REAL.

26:23.908 --> 26:25.707
IT'S NOT SOMETHING
I JUST -- I JUST THOUGHT UP.

26:25.709 --> 26:26.941
YOU CAME TO THE HOSPITAL
WITH AN AGENDA.

26:26.943 --> 26:27.942
YOU WANTED THIS
TO HAPPEN.

26:27.944 --> 26:28.742
SO DID YOU.

26:28.744 --> 26:29.909
NO, I DIDN'T.

26:29.911 --> 26:31.377
YOU GOT TO STOP
KIDDING YOURSELF.

26:31.379 --> 26:32.711
YOU LIKE THIS.

26:32.713 --> 26:33.912
<i> I</i> LIKE WHAT'S HAPPENING
BETWEEN US.

26:33.914 --> 26:35.313
BUT I'M WITH SOMEBODY.

26:35.315 --> 26:36.747
I HAVE A BOYFRIEND,
GUNNAR.

26:39.885 --> 26:42.552
YOU MAKE ME FEEL
LIKE I'M OUT OF CONTROL.

26:42.554 --> 26:45.421
YOU MAKE ME FEEL LIKE SOMEBODY
I DO NOT WANT TO BE.

26:45.423 --> 26:48.657
HE MAKES ME FEEL SAFE.

26:48.659 --> 26:49.824
AND I LOVE HIM.

26:49.826 --> 26:51.826
BUT YOU'RE NOT
<i> IN</i> LOVE WITH HIM.

26:51.828 --> 26:53.694
I'D LIKE TO BE.

26:53.696 --> 26:55.662
THEN WHY DO YOU KEEP
ENDING UP HERE WITH ME?

26:55.664 --> 26:57.663
[ SIGHS ]

26:59.366 --> 27:00.565
GOOD NIGHT.

27:00.567 --> 27:03.000
[<i> MUSIC CONTINUES</i> ]

27:03.002 --> 27:04.801
SCARLETT, DO--

27:04.803 --> 27:06.702
[ DOOR OPENS ]

27:08.372 --> 27:10.472
[<i> MUSIC ENDS</i> ]

27:10.474 --> 27:12.907
NO! NO!

27:12.909 --> 27:14.641
[ CRYING ]

27:16.645 --> 27:18.544
[ SNIFFLES, BREATHES DEEPLY ]

27:38.665 --> 27:39.997
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

27:39.999 --> 27:41.465
I'M GLAD YOU CALLED.

27:41.467 --> 27:43.700
THIS IS PERFECT.

27:43.702 --> 27:45.702
AND IT'S GOOD
TO SEE YOUR FACE AGAIN.

27:45.704 --> 27:47.403
THOUGHT YOU SAID
I COULD PULL OFF A BEARD.

27:47.405 --> 27:48.971
I WAS BEING NICE.

27:48.973 --> 27:50.906
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

27:50.908 --> 27:52.340
FAIR ENOUGH.

27:53.309 --> 27:54.775
WHAT?

27:54.777 --> 27:56.977
NOTHING.
I JUST, UM...

27:56.979 --> 28:00.479
JUST FEEL LIKE EVERYONE IN HERE
IS STARING AT ME.

28:01.682 --> 28:03.314
I THINK
YOU'RE BEING A LITTLE --

28:03.316 --> 28:05.549
I'M NOT BEING PARANOID.
THEY KNOW WHO I AM.

28:05.551 --> 28:06.550
THEY KNOW I'M --

28:06.552 --> 28:07.884
IGNORE THEM.

28:07.886 --> 28:11.053
WE'RE JUST HAVING DINNER.
IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

28:11.055 --> 28:13.188
YOU'RE A LIAR.

28:13.189 --> 28:15.322
I'M...SORRY.
DO WE KNOW EACH OTHER?

28:15.325 --> 28:16.857
WE SLEPT TOGETHER,
WHICH IS WEIRD,

28:16.859 --> 28:18.091
CONSIDERING YOU'RE GAY.

28:18.093 --> 28:20.326
THAT WOULD'VE BEEN
USEFUL INFORMATION TO HAVE

28:20.328 --> 28:21.960
BEFORE
I HUMILIATED MYSELF.

28:21.962 --> 28:24.395
YOU'RE DISGUSTING.

28:24.397 --> 28:25.729
HEY, GET BACK HERE --
LEAVE IT ALONE.

28:25.731 --> 28:27.363
LET'S JUST GO HOME.

28:27.365 --> 28:28.530
NO.

28:30.000 --> 28:31.499
LET'S GO SOMEWHERE
THIS WON'T HAPPEN.

28:33.069 --> 28:35.803
THESE ARE GREAT.
YOU GUYS, YOU GUYS, LOOK.

28:35.805 --> 28:38.372
"IF JULIETTE TWEETS ME BACK,
I WILL DIE.

28:38.374 --> 28:39.973
LOVE HER FOREVER,
EVER, EVER."

28:39.975 --> 28:41.374
AW.

28:41.376 --> 28:43.476
TELL HER I LOVE HER, TOO.
DON'T DIE.

28:43.478 --> 28:44.643
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
OKAY.

28:44.645 --> 28:47.078
OH!
LOOK -- YOUR FRIEND.

28:47.080 --> 28:49.113
HEY.
HEY, EVERYBODY.

28:49.115 --> 28:50.380
CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

28:50.382 --> 28:51.547
YEAH.

28:51.549 --> 28:52.548
GUYS, CAN I HAVE A SECOND,
PLEASE?

28:58.455 --> 28:59.454
HI.

28:59.456 --> 29:00.521
HI.

29:00.523 --> 29:01.788
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

29:01.790 --> 29:03.589
I GUESS I GOT
A LITTLE WORRIED ABOUT YOU

29:03.591 --> 29:05.724
AFTER THAT PHONE CALL
THIS MORNING.

29:05.726 --> 29:06.725
PHONE CALL?

29:06.727 --> 29:09.728
I DIDN'T CALL YOU,
DID I?

29:09.730 --> 29:11.896
MUST'VE BEEN A BUTT DIAL.
SORRY.

29:11.898 --> 29:13.631
ALL RIGHT, THIS IS
HOW YOU'RE GONNA PLAY THIS?

29:13.633 --> 29:15.099
'CAUSE YOU DEFINITELY
CALLED ME.

29:15.101 --> 29:16.967
YOU WERE CRYING.
YOU SAID MY NAME.

29:16.969 --> 29:18.401
IT WAS NOT A BUTT DIAL.

29:18.403 --> 29:19.668
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

29:19.670 --> 29:21.270
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN.

29:21.271 --> 29:22.871
YOU KNOW WE'VE HAD
OUR DIFFERENCES, FOR SURE,

29:22.873 --> 29:24.539
AND I KNOW YOU.

29:24.541 --> 29:26.641
I KNOW THAT HONEST
AND OPEN CONVERSATIONS

29:26.643 --> 29:28.643
ARE NOT
YOUR FAVORITE THING,

29:28.645 --> 29:30.611
BUT I FEEL LIKE YOU MIGHT
NEED A FRIEND RIGHT NOW.

29:32.014 --> 29:32.846
WHAT'S GOING ON?

29:32.848 --> 29:33.947
NOTHING.

29:33.949 --> 29:35.682
YOU CAN TALK TO ME.
I'M RIGHT HERE.

29:35.684 --> 29:37.417
JUST FLEW ALL THE WAY
ACROSS THE COUNTRY.

29:37.419 --> 29:39.152
I KNOW YOU'VE BEEN HAVING
SUCH A HARD TIME

29:39.154 --> 29:40.720
SINCE THE BABY WAS BORN,

29:40.722 --> 29:43.456
AND -- AND I UNDERSTAND
WHAT IT IS

29:43.458 --> 29:46.025
TO GO DOWN A ROAD WHERE IT SEEMS
LIKE NOTHING'S FAMILIAR.

29:46.027 --> 29:48.093
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

29:48.095 --> 29:50.028
YOU KNOW, YOU AND I HAVE KNOWN
EACH OTHER NOW FOR A LITTLE BIT.

29:50.030 --> 29:52.397
LET ME...

29:52.399 --> 29:54.932
LET ME HELP YOU
TRY TO FIND YOUR WAY BACK HOME.

29:54.934 --> 29:56.633
I<i> AM</i> HOME.

29:56.635 --> 29:58.101
COME ON --
YOU'RE JUST HERE

29:58.103 --> 29:59.902
BECAUSE YOU WANT ME
BACK ON YOUR LABEL, RIGHT?

29:59.904 --> 30:01.136
NO!

30:01.138 --> 30:02.937
I SIGNED THAT PAPERWORK
THIS MORNING.

30:02.939 --> 30:04.571
THAT SHIP HAS SAILED.

30:04.573 --> 30:06.673
BELIEVE IT OR NOT, I'M HERE
BECAUSE I CARE ABOUT YOU.

30:06.675 --> 30:08.107
I KNOW THAT YOU JUST WANT
A PIECE OF ME,

30:08.109 --> 30:09.575
JUST LIKE EVERYBODY ELSE.

30:09.577 --> 30:10.976
AT LEAST NOW
I'M ACTUALLY WORKING,

30:10.978 --> 30:13.577
UNLIKE WHEN I WAS WITH YOU
AT YOUR POINTLESS VANITY LABEL.

30:14.746 --> 30:17.446
ALL RIGHT,
FIRST OF ALL...

30:17.448 --> 30:19.681
HIGHWAY 65
ISN'T A VANITY LABEL.

30:19.683 --> 30:22.016
YOU HAD JUST HAD A BABY.

30:22.018 --> 30:24.118
I WAS TRYING
TO HELP YOU BALANCE EVERYTHING.

30:24.120 --> 30:26.954
I DON'T WANT YOUR HELP --
OR YOUR PITY, OKAY?

30:26.956 --> 30:29.022
I'M EXACTLY
WHERE I WANT TO BE.

30:29.024 --> 30:30.890
I'M ON THE TOP
OF THE WORLD.

30:30.892 --> 30:33.759
AND EVERYBODY KNOWS
THAT YOUR LABEL'S A JOKE.

30:33.761 --> 30:34.926
HEY,
DON'T PUSH ME AWAY.

30:34.928 --> 30:36.727
YOU HAVE NOTHING
TO OFFER ME.

30:36.729 --> 30:38.695
I DON'T EVEN UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU'RE HERE.

30:40.899 --> 30:43.065
YOU BREAK MY HEART,
GIRL.

30:43.067 --> 30:45.734
I SWEAR --
YOU REALLY DO.

30:47.771 --> 30:49.137
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

30:53.209 --> 30:54.508
I GOT CALEB'S TEXT.
I GOT HERE AS FAST AS I COULD.

30:54.510 --> 30:55.775
IS IT TRUE
SHE OPENED HER EYES?
YEP.

30:55.777 --> 30:57.576
SHE'S RESPONDING
TO HAND SQUEEZES, TOO.

30:57.578 --> 30:58.577
COME ON.

30:58.579 --> 31:00.912
MAMA, I'M HERE.

31:00.914 --> 31:02.113
[ Crying ]
OH, MY GOODNESS.

31:02.115 --> 31:04.515
[ LAUGHS ]

31:04.517 --> 31:06.650
[ COUGHS ]
DR. SUGRUE SAYS
HER C.A.T. SCAN'S LOOKING GOOD,

31:06.652 --> 31:08.585
AND SHE'S FIGHTING
THIS DAMN BREATHING TUBE,

31:08.587 --> 31:10.820
WHICH MEANS, UH --
SHE'S GONNA BE OKAY.

31:10.822 --> 31:12.221
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.
WELL, YEAH, THEY SAID
IT'S GONNA TAKE

31:12.223 --> 31:13.956
A COUPLE DAYS BEFORE SHE COMES
ALL THE WAY OUT OF IT,

31:13.958 --> 31:17.659
BUT, YEAH,
SHE'S GONNA BE OKAY.

31:17.661 --> 31:20.028
GOD, I'VE BEEN SO SCARED,
YOU KNOW?

31:20.030 --> 31:21.813
I DON'T EVEN THINK

31:21.814 --> 31:23.597
I EVEN EVER ADMITTED IT
TO MYSELF TILL RIGHT NOW,

31:23.600 --> 31:26.534
BUT IT'S JUST BEEN...
HELL.

31:26.536 --> 31:28.168
YEAH, IT HAS.

31:28.170 --> 31:30.837
YOUR MOM AND I HAD SUCH BAD
BLOOD BETWEEN US FOR SO LONG.

31:30.839 --> 31:32.805
ALWAYS SEEMED TO BRING OUT
THE WORST IN EACH OTHER.

31:32.807 --> 31:34.540
I ALWAYS THOUGHT
OUR RELATIONSHIP

31:34.542 --> 31:35.807
WAS GONNA BE JUST STUCK
THAT WAY, YOU KNOW?

31:35.809 --> 31:37.508
BUT IT ISN'T.
THAT'S JUST ME MAKING EXCUSES.

31:37.510 --> 31:39.476
I CAN CHANGE.

31:39.478 --> 31:40.576
NOW I GET TO.

31:43.013 --> 31:44.212
HONEY, YOU OKAY?

31:44.214 --> 31:46.881
MM-HMM.
[ SNIFFLES ]

31:46.883 --> 31:48.082
I'M GONNA GO CALL THE GIRLS,
ALL RIGHT?

31:48.084 --> 31:50.183
MM-HMM.
OKAY.

31:51.986 --> 31:54.987
[ COUGHS ]

31:54.989 --> 31:57.489
YOU'RE GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT.

32:04.898 --> 32:06.898
GET HER DOWN OKAY?

32:06.900 --> 32:08.799
YEAH.
TOOK THREE SONGS, BUT --

32:08.801 --> 32:10.767
PRETTY SOON,
IT'S GONNA BE THREE STORIES,

32:10.769 --> 32:12.201
THEN THREE GLASSES
OF WATER --

32:12.203 --> 32:14.036
JUST LIKE YOU.

32:14.038 --> 32:15.937
LISTEN.

32:15.939 --> 32:17.271
[ SIGHS ]

32:17.273 --> 32:19.239
I'VE, UH, BEEN THINKING
ABOUT YOUR OFFER.

32:20.141 --> 32:21.907
IF WE STAY HERE,

32:21.909 --> 32:24.509
I COULD TEACH CADENCE
HOW TO SWIM AT FIRST PRES,

32:24.511 --> 32:25.843
LIKE YOU TAUGHT<i> ME,</i>

32:25.845 --> 32:29.012
AND WE COULD HAVE SUNDAY DINNER
AS A FAMILY,

32:29.014 --> 32:31.247
I'D KNOW THE PARENTS OF EVERY
KID SHE GOES TO SCHOOL WITH.

32:31.249 --> 32:35.684
AND ALL OF THAT
IS VERY TEMPTING, BUT...

32:35.686 --> 32:40.788
YOU SEE,
WHEN CADENCE LOOKS AT ME...

32:40.790 --> 32:42.623
I DON'T WANT HER
TO SEE SOMEONE

32:42.625 --> 32:44.524
WHO GAVE UP HIS DREAMS
WITHOUT A FIGHT

32:44.526 --> 32:46.926
OR STOPPED
WORKING ON HIS MARRIAGE

32:46.928 --> 32:48.260
JUST BECAUSE
IT GOT HARD.

32:48.262 --> 32:49.728
AND I-I CAN'T TELL YOU

32:49.730 --> 32:52.030
HOW MUCH I APPRECIATE
ALL YOU'VE DONE FOR US.

32:52.032 --> 32:54.065
I CAN'T
KEEP HIDING HERE.

32:54.067 --> 32:56.200
NASHVILLE'S HOME NOW,

32:56.202 --> 32:59.136
WHETHER JULIETTE'S THERE
OR NOT.

33:00.205 --> 33:02.171
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

33:03.807 --> 33:04.872
THAT IS MINE!

33:04.874 --> 33:06.006
NO!
YOU THREW IT OUT!

33:06.007 --> 33:07.139
THAT DOESN'T MEAN
YOU GET TO READ IT!

33:07.142 --> 33:09.109
WELL,
WHAT IF IT HAD SOMETHING

33:09.110 --> 33:11.077
ABOUT YOU COMING TO VISIT DAD
BECAUSE YOU'RE OLDER?

33:11.079 --> 33:12.945
WE WOULDN'T EVEN KNOW, AND HE'D
BE WAITING FOR YOU TO COME.

33:12.947 --> 33:13.946
DID IT SAY THAT?

33:13.948 --> 33:15.814
NO.

33:15.816 --> 33:19.050
HE DOESN'T WANT US TO COME
VISIT HIM BECAUSE HE'S GUILTY.

33:19.052 --> 33:21.585
NO, HE ISN'T! HE'S GONNA
SHOW THEM THEY MESSED UP!

33:21.587 --> 33:23.119
YOU'RE SUCH A STUPID KID!
MADDIE!

33:23.121 --> 33:24.820
GET OFF!

33:24.822 --> 33:26.739
GIVE ME MY LETTER, DAPHNE!
SHUT UP!

33:26.740 --> 33:28.657
MADDIE!
HEY, COME ON, NOW!
CUT IT OUT, YOU TWO!

33:28.659 --> 33:29.824
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

33:29.826 --> 33:32.059
SHE STOLE MY LETTER,
AND SHE STARTED IT.

33:32.061 --> 33:33.861
ALL RIGHT, I DIDN'T ASK
WHO STARTED IT.

33:33.862 --> 33:35.662
ALL I KNOW IS Y'ALL GOT TO BE
NICER TO EACH OTHER.

33:35.664 --> 33:36.663
OKAY?
YOU HEAR ME?

33:36.665 --> 33:38.381
YOU MIGHT NOT KNOW THIS.

33:38.382 --> 33:40.098
THIS IS THE BEST FRIEND YOU'RE
EVER GONNA HAVE YOUR WHOLE LIFE.

33:43.637 --> 33:44.802
THAT GOES FOR YOU, TOO.

33:44.804 --> 33:47.104
YOU ARE NOT MY FATHER.

33:47.106 --> 33:49.106
YEAH, I KNOW THAT.

33:49.108 --> 33:51.074
JUST LIKE YOU KNOW
HOW MUCH I CARE ABOUT YOU,

33:51.076 --> 33:52.675
AND I ALWAYS HAVE.

33:52.677 --> 33:54.143
AND IF YOU NEED
TO TALK ABOUT SOMETHING WITH ME,

33:54.145 --> 33:55.677
WE CAN TALK ABOUT IT,
BUT --

34:02.985 --> 34:04.250
MAYBE YOU SHOULD
MARRY MOM.

34:04.252 --> 34:05.784
THEN SHE CAN'T SAY
STUFF LIKE THAT.

34:05.786 --> 34:07.619
[ CHUCKLES ]
YEAH, WELL, WE'RE GONNA.

34:07.621 --> 34:09.053
WE'RE JUST WAITING
FOR AUNT BEV TO GET BETTER

34:09.055 --> 34:10.821
SO SHE CAN
BE IN THE WEDDING.

34:14.359 --> 34:16.292
AND SHE'S GOING TO.

34:16.294 --> 34:18.927
I LOVE YOU, DAD.

34:18.929 --> 34:20.895
[ AFROJACK'S FEAT. EVA SIMMONS'
"TAKE OVER CONTROL" PLAYS ]

34:20.897 --> 34:23.330
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

34:25.701 --> 34:27.867
CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU BROUGHT ME TO A GAY BAR.

34:27.869 --> 34:29.368
WILL, IF YOU CAN'T FEEL
COMFORTABLE<i> HERE --</i>

34:29.370 --> 34:31.002
I KNOW, I KNOW.
I JUST --

34:31.004 --> 34:33.070
HEY, AT LEAST
NO ONE'S LOOKING AT YOU.

34:33.072 --> 34:35.205
COME ON. LET'S DANCE.

34:35.207 --> 34:37.240
ACTUALLY,
I-I DON'T REALLY FEEL LIKE --

34:37.242 --> 34:39.141
HEY, YOU'RE WITH ME.

34:39.143 --> 34:41.610
STOP THINKING SO MUCH.
IT'S OKAY TO HAVE FUN.

34:41.612 --> 34:45.379
¶ I WANT YOU TO TAKE OVER
CONTROL-OL-OL-OL ¶

34:45.381 --> 34:49.015
¶ PLUG IT IN AND TURN ME ON ¶

34:49.017 --> 34:50.850
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:02.797 --> 35:04.963
WHAT'S WRONG?

35:04.965 --> 35:06.731
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I -- I'M -- I'M SORRY.

35:06.733 --> 35:08.399
I J-- I -- EXCUSE ME.
EXCUSE ME.

35:08.401 --> 35:10.334
WILL!

35:10.335 --> 35:12.268
OH! IT'S JUST THE BEST NEWS
ABOUT BEVERLY. I'LL TELL YA.

35:12.271 --> 35:13.670
DEACON:
Yep, that's right.

35:13.672 --> 35:14.671
IT WAS A REAL GOOD DAY.

35:14.673 --> 35:16.339
Thank God.

35:16.340 --> 35:18.006
WISH I COULD SAY THE SAME,
BUT -- [ CHUCKLES ]

35:18.009 --> 35:19.074
WHAT HAPPENED?

35:19.076 --> 35:20.041
I don't know
why I did this.

35:20.043 --> 35:21.742
After all this time,

35:21.744 --> 35:23.844
I THINK I'M GONNA BE ABLE TO FIX
JULIETTE BARNES' PROBLEMS?

35:23.846 --> 35:25.045
NO.

35:25.047 --> 35:26.413
YEAH,
YOU CAN'T SAVE SOMEBODY

35:26.415 --> 35:28.014
WHEN THEY DON'T WANT
TO BE SAVED.

35:28.016 --> 35:29.715
YOU, OF ALL PEOPLE,
SHOULD KNOW THAT.

35:29.717 --> 35:31.116
YEAH, THAT'S FOR SURE.

35:31.118 --> 35:32.884
And there's nobody better
than Juliette

35:32.886 --> 35:35.386
at lashing out at the people
who care about her.

35:35.388 --> 35:38.255
I MEAN, SHE REALLY
GOES FOR THE JUGULAR.

35:38.257 --> 35:40.357
ANYWAY...
You sound tired.

35:40.359 --> 35:42.392
WHY DON'T YOU GET SOME SLEEP,
AND I'LL SEE YOU IN THE MORNING.

35:42.394 --> 35:43.926
I LOVE YOU.

35:43.928 --> 35:45.694
OH, I LOVE YOU, TOO.

36:07.150 --> 36:10.050
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

36:10.052 --> 36:11.418
[ DOOR OPENS ]

36:11.420 --> 36:13.453
HEY. SORRY.
I'M JUST LOOKING FOR PATRICK.

36:13.455 --> 36:14.854
THEY GUYS SAID
HE WAS IN HERE.

36:14.856 --> 36:15.921
HE'S NOT.

36:15.923 --> 36:17.389
AND WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

36:17.391 --> 36:19.958
JEFF GAVE ME PASSES
LAST WEEK.

36:19.960 --> 36:22.727
SO, I HEARD THAT STEVEN TYLER
WAS HERE TONIGHT.

36:22.729 --> 36:25.029
THAT'S COOL. DO YOU KNOW IF HE'S
GONNA BE AT THE AFTER PARTY?

36:25.031 --> 36:26.463
'CAUSE I WAS THINKING
THAT MAYBE WE COULD GO TOGETHER.

36:26.465 --> 36:27.997
YOU KNOW,
I KNOW THAT JEFF WOULD LOVE IT

36:27.999 --> 36:29.832
IF ALL THREE OF US
HAD OUR PICTURE TAKEN TOGETHER.

36:29.834 --> 36:31.767
YOU KNOW, AS A WOMAN,
IT PAINS ME

36:31.769 --> 36:35.170
TO SEE YOU HAVE
SO LITTLE SELF-RESPECT.

36:35.172 --> 36:36.804
[ SCOFFS ] WHAT?

36:36.806 --> 36:40.007
YOU IN BED WITH JEFF FORDHAM --
LITERALLY?

36:40.009 --> 36:41.708
YOU MUST HATE YOURSELF.

36:41.710 --> 36:42.942
YOU DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT HIM.

36:42.944 --> 36:45.244
YOU DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT ME, OKAY?

36:45.246 --> 36:46.478
JEFF IS ACTUALLY...

36:46.480 --> 36:48.079
A TERRIBLE HUMAN BEING.

36:48.081 --> 36:49.480
BUT, UNLIKE YOU,
I WAS SMART ENOUGH

36:49.482 --> 36:52.182
TO MAKE SURE
IT WAS A ONE-TIME THING.

36:54.819 --> 36:57.820
YOU MAY HAVE JUST BEEN
A PIECE OF ASS TO HIM,

36:57.822 --> 36:59.855
BUT HE LOVES ME.

36:59.857 --> 37:01.089
AND I LOVE HIM.

37:01.091 --> 37:03.858
OH, MY GOD.
[ LAUGHS ]

37:03.860 --> 37:06.193
I DIDN'T THINK
I COULD THINK ANY LESS OF YOU,

37:06.195 --> 37:08.495
BUT THERE YOU GO,
MAKING IT HAPPEN.

37:08.497 --> 37:10.964
YOU THINK YOU LOVE HIM?

37:10.966 --> 37:12.131
YOU THINK HE LOVES YOU?

37:12.133 --> 37:13.198
RIGHT.

37:13.200 --> 37:14.732
WELL,
AT THE END OF THE DAY,

37:14.734 --> 37:17.434
WHO DO YOU THINK
HE'S GONNA PUT FIRST?

37:17.436 --> 37:19.202
ME -- NOT YOU.

37:19.204 --> 37:21.804
YOU'RE JUST HERE
TRYING TO PROVE TO THE WORLD

37:21.806 --> 37:24.973
THAT YOU'RE SOMETHING OTHER THAN
A FAILED REALITY STAR.

37:24.975 --> 37:26.441
YOU'RE NOT ME, HONEY.

37:26.443 --> 37:27.975
YOU'RE NEVER GONNA BE ME.

37:27.977 --> 37:29.176
GOOD.

37:29.178 --> 37:30.977
YEAH. GOOD.

37:33.748 --> 37:36.281
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

37:42.254 --> 37:43.519
[ DANCE MUSIC PLAYS ]
WILL!

37:43.521 --> 37:45.387
I'VE BEEN LOOKING EVERYWHERE
FOR YOU.

37:45.389 --> 37:48.857
HEY! WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

37:48.859 --> 37:50.391
LOOK, I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE GOING THROUGH.

37:50.393 --> 37:52.159
COMING OUT,
IT'S -- IT'S A LONG PROCESS,

37:52.161 --> 37:53.059
BUT I PROMISE YOU --

37:53.061 --> 37:54.760
THIS ISN'T ME.

37:54.762 --> 37:57.529
DANCING TO ELECTRONICA MUSIC --
IT -- IT ISN'T ME.

37:57.531 --> 37:59.297
OKAY, THEN, W-WE'LL GO
SOMEPLACE ELSE, THEN.

37:59.299 --> 38:01.432
WHERE? I DON'T BELONG
IN MY OLD PLACES.

38:01.434 --> 38:02.933
I-I DON'T BELONG
IN THERE.

38:04.770 --> 38:05.802
I DON'T BELONG.

38:10.007 --> 38:11.539
I'LL, UH...

38:11.541 --> 38:14.474
I'LL TALK TO YOU
SOMETIME TOMORROW, OKAY?

38:15.410 --> 38:16.509
¶ CAN YOU HOLD ME UP? ¶

38:16.511 --> 38:18.310
[ WOMEN SCREAM ]

38:18.312 --> 38:19.411
CHEERS.

38:19.413 --> 38:20.779
¶ SO HOLD ME UP... ¶

38:20.781 --> 38:22.046
MMM! WHOO!

38:22.048 --> 38:24.114
YOU WERE INCREDIBLE.

38:24.116 --> 38:25.515
I WANT LAYLA GONE.

38:25.517 --> 38:26.649
WHAT?

38:26.650 --> 38:27.782
SEND HER BACK
TO NASHVILLE,

38:27.785 --> 38:29.417
PUSH HER IN FRONT
OF ONCOMING TRAFFIC --

38:29.419 --> 38:30.902
I DON'T CARE,
AS LONG AS I NEVER

38:30.903 --> 38:32.386
HAVE TO LOOK AT THAT SMUG
LITTLE FACE AGAIN.

38:32.388 --> 38:33.887
JULIETTE,
JEFF WANTS HER HERE.

38:33.889 --> 38:35.388
WHO IS
YOUR BIGGEST CLIENT?

38:36.791 --> 38:38.223
WE'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.
WHATEVER YOU WANT.

38:38.225 --> 38:40.058
OKAY.

38:40.060 --> 38:42.060
[ GLASSES CLINK ]

38:42.062 --> 38:43.828
<i>Leave your message at the tone.</i>

38:43.830 --> 38:45.146
[ BEEP ]

38:45.147 --> 38:46.463
HEY, JEFF.
IT'S ME AGAIN.

38:46.465 --> 38:48.264
THE MEETING WITH VALERIE
WENT REALLY WELL.

38:48.266 --> 38:50.566
I GUESS IT'S A GOOD THING
I CAME OUT TO L.A.

38:51.902 --> 38:56.203
LISTEN, I KNOW YOU'RE [SIGHS]
MANAGING JULIETTE, TOO, BUT --

38:56.205 --> 38:58.004
AND, YOU KNOW, SHE'S A BIGGER
STAR THAN ME AND EVERYTHING,

38:58.006 --> 39:00.539
BUT I JUST --
I NEED YOU TO REMIND ME

39:00.541 --> 39:04.575
THAT I'M NUMBER ONE FOR YOU...

39:04.577 --> 39:06.476
[ Voice breaking ]
WHEN IT COUNTS.

39:06.478 --> 39:07.844
[ SIGHS ] HEY.

39:07.846 --> 39:08.511
HEY.

39:08.513 --> 39:10.196
WHERE'S SCARLETT?

39:10.197 --> 39:11.880
UH, WE SHOULD PROBABLY TALK
BEFORE WE RECORD.

39:11.883 --> 39:12.581
YEP, SHE ALREADY DID.

39:12.583 --> 39:13.982
WHAT?

39:13.984 --> 39:15.083
YEAH, SHE LEFT
ABOUT AN HOUR AGO.

39:15.085 --> 39:16.084
WE LAID DOWN HER TRACKS.

39:16.086 --> 39:17.085
WITHOUT ME?

39:17.087 --> 39:18.386
[ SCOFFS ]

39:18.388 --> 39:20.020
DID I MISUNDERSTAND?

39:20.022 --> 39:21.421
WAS SHE GONNA COME BACK?

39:21.423 --> 39:22.989
NO, I GUESS NOT.

39:24.926 --> 39:27.359
LET'S JUST, UH,
GET THIS DONE.

39:27.361 --> 39:29.260
[ "WAKE ME WHEN IT'S OVER"
PLAYS ]

39:39.371 --> 39:43.439
Scarlett:
¶ IT WASN'T ONE BIG BLOW
THAT BROUGHT OUR LOVE DOWN ¶

39:45.543 --> 39:50.379
¶ IT WAS THE HAIRLINE CRACKS
THAT TOOK IT TO THE GROUND ¶

39:51.615 --> 39:55.316
¶ JUST KEPT CREEPIN'
OVER TIME ¶

39:55.318 --> 39:58.052
¶ SPREADIN' LIKE WILDFIRE ¶

39:58.054 --> 40:02.288
¶ IT WASN'T ONE BIG BLOW
THAT BROUGHT OUR LOVE DOWN ¶

40:05.192 --> 40:09.393
Gunnar and Scarlett:
¶ OOH, YOU DIDN'T WANT TO SEE ¶

40:09.395 --> 40:12.396
¶ DIDN'T WANT TO BELIEVE ¶

40:12.398 --> 40:17.200
¶ THE DREAMS GETTING COLDER ¶

40:17.202 --> 40:18.634
THERE'S SOMETHING
I NEED TO TELL YOU.

40:18.636 --> 40:21.036
¶ OOH, WE BEGGED THE TRUTH
TO BEND ¶

40:21.038 --> 40:22.037
I LOVE YOU.

40:22.039 --> 40:23.104
¶ IT'S EASIER TO PRETEND ¶

40:23.106 --> 40:24.939
[ CHUCKLES ]
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

40:24.941 --> 40:28.175
¶ THAN TO SEE
WHEN YOU'RE SOBER ¶

40:30.946 --> 40:34.280
¶ YOU ONLY WAKE UP
WHEN IT'S OVER ¶

40:36.017 --> 40:40.318
¶ OOH, YOU ONLY WAKE UP
WHEN IT'S OVER ¶

40:43.289 --> 40:48.458
¶ YOU ONLY WAKE UP
WHEN IT'S OVER ¶

40:48.460 --> 40:50.193
<i> THAT WAS SOME</i>
<i> OF YOUR BEST STUFF, MAN.</i>

40:50.195 --> 40:52.145
<i> DIDN'T EVEN MATTER</i>

40:52.146 --> 40:54.096
<i> THAT YOU WEREN'T HERE</i>
<i> RECORDING TOGETHER.</i>

40:54.098 --> 40:55.564
<i> COME ON IN.</i>

41:00.937 --> 41:03.103
IT WASN'T THE SAME.

41:03.105 --> 41:04.571
[<i> THEME MUSIC PLAYS</i> ]

41:04.573 --> 41:06.639
Man on radio:
<i> GOOD MORNING, NASHVILLE!</i>

41:06.641 --> 41:08.607
<i> COMING UP NEXT --</i>
<i> A LITTLE JULIETTE BARNES.</i>

41:08.609 --> 41:10.842
<i> SHE REALLY LIT UP</i>
<i> THE RED CARPET</i>

41:10.843 --> 41:13.076
<i> THE OTHER NIGHT IN HOLLYWOOD</i>
<i> AT HER FIRST MOVIE PREMIERE.</i>

41:14.547 --> 41:16.113
[ SIGHS ]

41:16.115 --> 41:17.948
Gunnar:
FIGURED YOU BE AT KEVIN'S.

41:17.950 --> 41:19.349
NOPE.

41:19.351 --> 41:21.451
YOU TWO HAVE A FIGHT?

41:21.453 --> 41:23.586
UH, JUST A BAD NIGHT.

41:23.588 --> 41:25.872
HOW ABOUT YOURS?

41:25.873 --> 41:28.157
WELL, SCARLETT ADMITTED
SHE FEELS SOMETHING FOR ME,

41:28.159 --> 41:30.926
BUT...SHE'S GONNA STAY
WITH CALEB.

41:30.928 --> 41:32.627
SO, NOT GOOD.

41:32.628 --> 41:34.327
YEAH, IT KIND OF SUCKS.
[ CHUCKLES ]
RIGHT.

41:36.098 --> 41:37.230
AH. HEY, BUDDY.

41:37.232 --> 41:39.532
HEY, HEY.
HEY.

41:39.534 --> 41:41.133
UH...

41:41.135 --> 41:42.300
OH, YEAH,
I FORGOT TO TELL YOU.

41:42.302 --> 41:45.636
UM...
WE GOT A NEW ROOMMATE.

41:45.638 --> 41:48.071
TWO, IN FACT.

41:48.073 --> 41:51.174
[ CADENCE COOING ]

41:51.176 --> 41:53.042
Man on radio:<i> AND THAT WAS</i>
<i> JULIETTE BARNES' NEW SINGLE,</i>

41:53.044 --> 41:54.464
<i> "MISSISSIPPI FLOOD."</i>

41:54.465 --> 41:55.885
Woman on radio:
<i> LOVE THAT ONE.</i>

41:55.886 --> 41:57.306
<i> AND SHE'LL BE STOPPING BY</i>
<i> NEXT WEEK</i>

41:57.307 --> 41:58.727
<i> TO TALK TO US</i>
<i> ABOUT HER NEW ALBUM.</i>

41:58.728 --> 42:00.148
<i> YEAH, IF SHE HAS TIME</i>
<i> FOR US LITTLE PEOPLE.</i>

42:00.150 --> 42:02.583
<i> [ LAUGHS</i> ]<i> RAYNA JAMES MUST BE</i>
<i> KICKING HERSELF PRETTY HARD</i>

42:02.585 --> 42:03.907
<i> FOR LETTING JULIETTE GO.</i>

42:03.908 --> 42:05.230
<i> I TELL YOU,</i>
<i> RAYNA HASN'T DONE SO WELL</i>

42:05.231 --> 42:06.553
<i> WITH THE TALENT SHE SIGNED</i>
<i> TO HER LABEL.</i>

42:06.555 --> 42:08.005
<i> NO, SHE HASN'T.</i>

42:08.006 --> 42:09.456
<i> FIRST, THERE WAS</i>
<i> SCARLETT O'CONNOR,</i>

42:09.457 --> 42:10.907
<i> WHO HAD THAT MELTDOWN</i>
<i> ONSTAGE.</i>

42:10.908 --> 42:12.358
<i> RIGHT, THEN SADIE STONE</i>
<i> KILLED HER HUSBAND.</i>

42:12.360 --> 42:13.692
<i> THEN JULIETTE LEFT.</i>

42:13.694 --> 42:15.393
<i> YEAH, BASICALLY,</i>
<i> RAYNA'S 0 FOR 3</i>

42:15.395 --> 42:17.495
<i> AT LAUNCHING ANYONE</i>
<i> OTHER THAN HERSELF.</i>

42:17.497 --> 42:19.330
<i> I TELL YOU,</i>
<i> I LOVE ME SOME RAYNA,</i>

42:19.332 --> 42:22.099
<i> BUT SOME STARS JUST DON'T KNOW</i>
<i> HOW TO RUN A BUSINESS.</i>
